,"target":"rec8DcjjipTJqZu2m","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recdhRSAgJbeIgSWR","target":"recRnjWuL5tcXfusW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recdhRSAgJbeIgSWR","target":"recsX4et9ux7g07Zg","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recH6lP6Rq0amIqUk","ref":"Num.21.1","text":"And when king Arad the Canaanite, which dwelt in the south, heard tell that Israel came by the way of the spies; then he fought against Israel, and took some of them prisoners.","year":-1453},{"id":"recygSIzwJLmnuoyA","ref":"Num.21.2","text":"And Israel vowed a vow unto the LORD, and said, If thou wilt indeed deliver this people into my hand, then I will utterly destroy their cities.","year":-1453},{"id":"recMyciaDOXJZR4Ch","ref":"Num.21.3","text":"And the LORD hearkened to the voice of Israel, and delivered up the Canaanites; and they utterly destroyed them and their cities: and he called the name of the place Hormah.","year":-1453},{"id":"recYSkoP2mcjk07e1","ref":"Num.21.4","text":"And they journeyed from mount Hor by the way of the Red sea, to compass the land of Edom: and the soul of the people was much discouraged because of the way.","year":-1453},{"id":"rec4S2loHH3sm0jPr","ref":"Num.21.5","text":"And the people spake against God, and against Moses, Wherefore have ye brought us up out of Egypt to die in the wilderness? for there is no bread, neither is there any water; and our soul loatheth this light bread.","year":-1453},{"id":"recAFmuz4LeihIPyV","ref":"Num.21.6","text":"And the LORD sent fiery serpents among the people, and they bit the people; and much people of Israel died.","year":-1453},{"id":"recVJOyvxWAnX1DMs","ref":"Num.21.7","text":"Therefore the people came to Moses, and said, We have sinned, for we have spoken against the LORD, and against thee; pray unto the LORD, that he take away the serpents from us. And Moses prayed for the people.","year":-1453},{"id":"recnE7yStYMUEiMTl","ref":"Num.21.8","text":"And the LORD said unto Moses, Make thee a fiery serpent, and set it upon a pole: and it shall come to pass, that every one that is bitten, when he looketh upon it, shall live.","year":-1453}]}
